1) POLICY RULES:
- If the action cell is empty (.), click to draw (seen in ~3/10 demos).
- If the action cell is a target (T), click to draw (seen in ~5/10 demos).
- If the action cell is an agent (A), do not click (seen in ~4/10 demos).
- If the action cell is a wall (#), do not click (seen in ~10/10 demos).
- If there is a target (T) directly above the action cell, click the action cell (seen in ~2/10 demos).
- If there is an agent (A) directly below the action cell, do not click (seen in ~3/10 demos).
- If there is a drawn cell (*) directly to the left of the action cell, do not click (seen in ~2/10 demos).
- If there is a target (T) directly to the right of the action cell, click the action cell (seen in ~1/10 demos).

2) COUNTERFACTUAL DISTRACTORS:
- If the action cell is a wall (#), do not click (seen in ~10/10 demos).
- If there is a drawn cell (*) directly below the action cell, do not click (seen in ~2/10 demos).
- If there is a target (T) directly below the action cell, do not click (seen in ~1/10 demos).
- If there is an agent (A) directly to the right of the action cell, do not click (seen in ~3/10 demos).
- If there is a target (T) directly to the left of the action cell, do not click (seen in ~1/10 demos).

3) GAME DYNAMICS:
- Clicking on a target (T) changes it to an empty cell (.) (seen in ~5/10 demos).
- Clicking on an empty cell (.) changes it to a drawn cell (*) (seen in ~3/10 demos).
- Clicking on an agent (A) changes it to an empty cell (.) (seen in ~4/10 demos).
- Clicking on a wall (#) has no effect (seen in ~10/10 demos).
- Clicking on an arrow (e.g., >, <, ^, v) can cause movement of the agent (A) in the direction of the arrow (seen in ~3/10 demos).

4) TOKEN MAP:
TOKEN_MAP = {
  "#": "ec.WALL",
  "*": "ec.DRAWN",
